---
import Layout from '@layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy — Orbitcheck"
  description="Learn how Orbitcheck handles your data privacy and complies with regulations."
  canonical="https://orbitcheck.io/legal/privacy"
>
  <main class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-900">
    <article class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-extrabold">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
        This Privacy Policy explains how Orbitcheck ("Orbitcheck," "we," "us,"
        or "our") collects, uses, discloses, and protects Personal Data when you
        visit our websites, use our APIs, SDKs, connectors, and dashboards (the
        "Services"), or otherwise interact with us. It also describes your
        privacy rights and how to exercise them.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-2 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
        If you require a countersigned copy or have questions, contact <a
          href="mailto:privacy@orbitcheck.io"
          class="text-indigo-700 hover:underline dark:text-indigo-400"
          >privacy@orbitcheck.io</a
        >.
      </p>

      <div
        class="mt-6 rounded-md border border-gray-200 bg-gray-100 p-4 dark:bg-gray-800 dark:border-gray-700"
      >
        <p class="font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200">
          Highlights:
        </p>
        <ul
          class="list-disc pl-6 mt-2 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 space-y-1"
        >
          <li>
            We process end-customer data on your instructions to validate
            addresses, phones, emails, and business/tax IDs.
          </li>
          <li>
            We do not sell or share Personal Data for cross-context behavioral
            advertising.
          </li>
          <li>
            Data retention is configurable by plan (typically 7–365 days);
            caches and logs are short-lived.
          </li>
          <li>
            Strong security: encryption in transit and at rest, access controls,
            monitoring, and incident response.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <h2 id="scope" class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8">
        1. Who We Are and Scope
      </h2>
      <p class="mt-2 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
        Orbitcheck provides API-first data hygiene and validation for ecommerce:
        addresses, phones, emails, EU VAT, and ES–LATAM tax IDs with
        deduplication, entity resolution, and risk-driven order controls.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-2 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
        This Policy applies to: (a) visitors to our websites and people who
        interact with our marketing or sales (we act as a controller); and (b)
        customers and their end users whose Personal Data is submitted to the
        Services (we generally act as a processor/service provider on behalf of
        our customers). For processor activities, our <a
          href="/legal/dpa"
          class="text-indigo-700 hover:underline dark:text-indigo-400"
          >Data Processing Addendum</a
        > governs.
      </p>

      <h2 id="data-we-collect" class="text-xl font-semibold mt-6">
        2. Personal Data We Collect
      </h2>
      <p class="mt-2 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
        The Personal Data we process depends on how you interact with us and
        which features you use.
      </p>
      <ul
        class="list-disc pl-6 mt-2 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 space-y-2"
      >
        <li>
          <strong>Account and Contact Data</strong>: name, company, role, email,
          phone, login identifiers, workspace/user IDs.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Service (Customer) Data</strong>: data you submit to validate
          or deduplicate, such as names, emails, phone numbers, shipping/billing
          addresses, and supported identifiers (e.g., EU VAT IDs, ES NIF/NIE, BR
          CPF/CNPJ, MX RFC, AR CUIT, CL RUT, PE RUC/DNI). We also generate
          structured reason codes, match scores, and risk signals.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Transaction and Billing Data</strong>: subscription tier,
          invoices, tax/VAT numbers, and payment status. Card data is processed
          by our payment processor; we do not store full card numbers.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Technical and Usage Data</strong>: IP address,
          device/browser/user agent, API keys/IDs, request metadata, logs,
          diagnostics, and event telemetry needed to secure and operate the
          Services.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Support Content</strong>: information you send to support,
          including attachments or screenshots.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2 id="how-we-use" class="text-xl font-semibold mt-6">
        3. How We Use Personal Data
      </h2>
      <ul
        class="list-disc pl-6 mt-2 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 space-y-2"
      >
        <li>
          Provide, maintain, validate, deduplicate, and improve the Services.
        </li>
        <li>
          Secure the Services, prevent abuse and fraud, and ensure integrity and
          availability.
        </li>
        <li>Operate account management, billing, and customer support.</li>
        <li>
          Develop new features and perform analytics using de-identified or
          aggregated data.
        </li>
        <li>
          Send service and transactional communications; send product updates or
          marketing where permitted.
        </li>
        <li>Comply with legal obligations and enforce terms.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 id="sharing" class="text-xl font-semibold mt-6">
        4. How We Share Personal Data
      </h2>
      <ul
        class="list-disc pl-6 mt-2 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 space-y-2"
      >
        <li>
          <strong>Subprocessors/Service Providers</strong> that host, store, or process
          data for us.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Integrations You Authorize</strong> (e.g., Shopify/Woo/BigCommerce
          connectors).
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Professional Advisors</strong> (legal, auditors) under confidentiality.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Legal/Compliance</strong> when required by law or to protect rights
          and safety.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Corporate Transactions</strong> (merger, acquisition, financing).
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p class="mt-2 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
        We do <strong>not</strong> sell or share Personal Data for cross-context
        behavioral advertising.
      </p>

      <h2 id="retention" class="text-xl font-semibold mt-6">5. Retention</h2>
      <p class="mt-2 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
        We retain Personal Data only as long as necessary for the purposes
        described. For Service Data, retention is configurable by plan
        (typically 7–365 days). Ephemeral caches and logs are short-lived and
        purged regularly.
      </p>

      <h2 id="your-rights" class="text-xl font-semibold mt-6">
        6. Your Privacy Rights
      </h2>
      <p class="mt-2 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
        Depending on your location, you may have rights to request: access,
        correction, deletion, restriction, portability, and to object to certain
        processing. We honor browser-based Global Privacy Control (GPC) signals
        where legally required.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-2 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
        To exercise your rights, contact <a
          href="mailto:privacy@orbitcheck.io"
          class="text-indigo-700 hover:underline dark:text-indigo-400"
          >privacy@orbitcheck.io</a
        >.
      </p>

      <h2 id="contact" class="text-xl font-semibold mt-6">7. Contact Us</h2>
      <p class="mt-2 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
        Questions, requests, or complaints:<br />
        Email: <a
          href="mailto:privacy@orbitcheck.io"
          class="text-indigo-700 hover:underline dark:text-indigo-400"
          >privacy@orbitcheck.io</a
        ><br />
        Security incidents: <a
          href="mailto:security@orbitcheck.io"
          class="text-indigo-700 hover:underline dark:text-indigo-400"
          >security@orbitcheck.io</a
        >
      </p>

      <h2 id="links" class="text-xl font-semibold mt-6">Related Documents</h2>
      <ul
        class="list-disc pl-6 mt-2 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 space-y-2"
      >
        <li>
          <a
            href="/legal/tos"
            class="text-indigo-700 hover:underline dark:text-indigo-400"
            >Terms of Service</a
          >
        </li>
        <li>
          <a
            href="/legal/dpa"
            class="text-indigo-700 hover:underline dark:text-indigo-400"
            >Data Processing Addendum (DPA)</a
          >
        </li>
      </ul>

      <p class="mt-10 text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">
        Last updated: 2025-10-16
      </p>
    </article>
  </main>
</Layout>
